      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1016648/" class="title-link">An Underground Education</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1016648"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/1058831/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1058831-6.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/1058831/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">Emilysu</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2005-12-24"
      class="main-meta">2005-12-24 14:05:07</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1016648_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  “历史时而令人发抖，时而令人发笑”      作者在揭露被历史学家们试图掩盖的真相。其实历史就是这样，并不多么高尚；可如果历史就是这样，那我们现在的一幕幕丑闻也是很合理的；而今天我们看来合理的事，明天再看，不过是一出闹剧而已。既然这样，我们应该怎样才能避免做错事...

